WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:04.186
♪ My name is Cleveland Brown

00:04.188 --> 00:06.455
♪ And I am proud to be

00:06.457 --> 00:08.841
♪ Right back
In my hometown ♪

00:08.843 --> 00:11.227
♪ With my new family

00:11.229 --> 00:13.412
♪ There's old friends
And new friends ♪

00:13.414 --> 00:15.814
♪ And even a bear

00:15.816 --> 00:17.983
♪ Through good times
And bad times ♪

00:17.985 --> 00:19.618
♪ It's true love we share

00:19.620 --> 00:21.587
♪ And so I found a place

00:21.589 --> 00:23.990
♪ Where everyone will know

00:23.992 --> 00:26.359
♪ My happy mustache face

00:26.361 --> 00:28.377
♪ This is <i>The Cleveland Show</i> ♪

00:28.379 --> 00:30.679
[LAUGHS]

00:30.681 --> 00:32.498
[♪]

00:42.309 --> 00:44.926
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>And that makes</i>
<i>six wins in a row</i>

00:44.928 --> 00:46.595
<i>for Stoolbend High baseball</i>

00:46.597 --> 00:49.598
<i>under the leadership</i>
<i>of Coach Clarence Brown.</i>

00:49.600 --> 00:51.600
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>It's Cleveland Brown,</i>

00:51.602 --> 00:56.021
who hasn't seen the postseason
<i>since his playing days in 1984.</i>

00:56.023 --> 00:58.190
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>Aseveryone knows,</i>
<i>that was the year</i>

00:58.192 --> 01:01.127
<i>the Growlers lost state</i>
<i>to the Mud Falls Trotters,</i>

01:01.129 --> 01:04.096
<i>General Motors shut down</i>
<i>the plant, little Missy White</i>

01:04.098 --> 01:05.731
was found bludgeoned to death,

01:05.733 --> 01:08.417
<i>and Stoolbend's been</i>
<i>in the crapper ever since.</i>

01:08.419 --> 01:11.570
And on a personal note,
that was the year I tried sushi.

01:11.572 --> 01:14.072
Didn't like it.
Never tried it again.

01:14.074 --> 01:15.707
<i>Hey, Angus.</i>
<i>Here's a question.</i>

01:15.709 --> 01:17.442
<i>Which woman</i>
<i>on</i> Friday Night Lights

01:17.444 --> 01:18.944
<i>wouldn't you have sex with?</i>

01:18.946 --> 01:19.878
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>The mayor.</i>

01:19.880 --> 01:21.630
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>We'll accept that.</i>

01:21.632 --> 01:25.167
The mayor or Saracen's grandma,
<i>the only two possible answers.</i>

01:25.169 --> 01:27.803
<i>Go Growlers.</i>

01:27.805 --> 01:30.973
[CHEERING]

01:30.975 --> 01:33.342
Betting on the Growlers
is winning me a fortune.

01:33.344 --> 01:36.178
Last week, I made my first
charitable donation.

01:36.180 --> 01:38.647
A hundred dollars
to Fight the Cure.

01:38.649 --> 01:40.649
Don't you mean
Find the Cure?

01:40.651 --> 01:42.418
Nope. Fight the Cure.

01:42.420 --> 01:45.120
It's America's only
pro-AIDS charity.

01:45.122 --> 01:47.356
If I got it,
everyone's gotta have it.

01:47.358 --> 01:49.759
What makes you think
you have AIDS?

01:49.761 --> 01:52.661
I watched the Madonna
episode of <i>Glee.</i>

01:52.663 --> 01:54.280
[LAUGHS]

01:54.282 --> 01:57.416
You are an ignorant man.

01:57.418 --> 01:59.134
Hey, let's hear it
for Cleveland,

01:59.136 --> 02:00.870
who's gonna give my son,
Raymond,

02:00.872 --> 02:04.339
some playing time
in the playoffs.

02:04.341 --> 02:06.925
Don't worry, Tim,
I'll put him in next game.

02:06.927 --> 02:09.428
Really?
No. Not even considering it.

02:09.430 --> 02:11.263
Raymond's a bad player.

02:11.265 --> 02:12.848
Wha--? He is?

02:12.850 --> 02:14.617
Cleveland, let me know
what I can do.

02:14.619 --> 02:16.085
Holt Richter
reporting for duty.

02:16.087 --> 02:17.686
MVP of my little league team.

02:17.688 --> 02:20.889
You mean your very
little league?

02:20.891 --> 02:23.625
Ha! We devalue you
and your accomplishments

02:23.627 --> 02:25.094
due to your size.

02:25.096 --> 02:26.862
[ALL LAUGH]

02:26.864 --> 02:28.463
[CLAPPING]

02:32.201 --> 02:33.019
Who is that?

02:33.021 --> 02:36.121
Chet Butler,
my long-time rival

02:36.123 --> 02:39.458
that you're just hearing about
now for the first time.

02:39.460 --> 02:42.962
That dirty-playing S.O.B.
purposely beaned me

02:42.964 --> 02:44.597
and knocked me
out of the game,

02:44.599 --> 02:46.832
costing us
the championship.

02:46.834 --> 02:50.603
I still have the scar
from where that pitch hit me.

02:54.274 --> 02:58.277
So, what brings your
slow-clapping ass into my bar?

02:58.279 --> 03:00.262
Just taking my state
championship ring

03:00.264 --> 03:01.864
out for a little walk.

03:03.500 --> 03:06.836
Of course, you'll never know
what that feels like, loser.

03:06.838 --> 03:11.106
Yeah, well, you'll never know
what losing feels like, winner.

03:11.108 --> 03:13.709
[ALL CHEERING]

03:13.711 --> 03:16.779
You've won this round,
Cleveland.

03:16.781 --> 03:20.299
So I guess I do know
what losing feels like.

03:20.301 --> 03:22.000
ALL:
Ooh!

03:22.002 --> 03:24.002
I'm, uh, gonna go get a beer.

03:24.004 --> 03:25.605
[CROWD CHEERING]

03:25.607 --> 03:27.439
Well, I guess the crowd's
reaction

03:27.441 --> 03:28.874
isn't really
a good indication

03:28.876 --> 03:30.342
of whose side they're on.

03:30.344 --> 03:33.946
ALL:
<i>Wheel of Fortune.</i>

03:33.948 --> 03:37.716
[♪]

03:37.718 --> 03:40.953
So, Junior, how's your wood shop
project going?

03:40.955 --> 03:42.538
Whee!

03:42.540 --> 03:44.773
I'm making sawdust angels.

03:44.775 --> 03:46.208
That's your project?

03:46.210 --> 03:47.843
Who cares? It's shop.

03:47.845 --> 03:49.477
It's not like a real class.

03:49.479 --> 03:51.346
MAN:
Not a real class?

03:51.348 --> 03:54.482
I'm sorry.
I didn't see you, Mr. Thumbs.

03:54.484 --> 03:56.034
[ALL GASP]

03:56.036 --> 03:57.786
That's what we call him
behind his back.

03:57.788 --> 04:00.155
You think these are funny?

04:00.157 --> 04:01.807
I can't walk down
the damn street

04:01.809 --> 04:06.345
without people pulling over
and asking if I need a ride.

04:06.347 --> 04:08.046
They think
you're hitchhiking.

04:08.048 --> 04:09.982
You better get serious,
young fella.

04:09.984 --> 04:12.902
This project is worth 75 percent
of your grade.

04:12.904 --> 04:14.987
We get a grade in this class?

04:14.989 --> 04:18.691
Wha--? If I fail shop,
I'll disappoint my father.

04:18.693 --> 04:21.226
And I've never disappointed
my father.

04:21.228 --> 04:22.511
Get your act together, Brown.

04:22.513 --> 04:24.680
If your final project
doesn't blow me away,

04:24.682 --> 04:27.916
I will not hesitate
to give you an F.

04:27.918 --> 04:29.267
You would F me?

04:29.269 --> 04:32.070
Well, how do you even
write down grades?

04:32.072 --> 04:33.672
I report them orally.

04:33.674 --> 04:34.840
That's right.

04:34.842 --> 04:39.244
I will F you orally.

04:39.246 --> 04:42.047
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>And the Growlers winning big</i>
<i>in a blowout,</i>

04:42.049 --> 04:44.583
<i>thanks to a strong outing</i>
<i>by deaf pitcher,</i>

04:44.585 --> 04:46.552
<i>Oliver Wilkerson.</i>

04:46.554 --> 04:48.203
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>Okay, people, on your feet,</i>

04:48.205 --> 04:52.324
<i>because it's time to welcome</i>
<i>the Growler himself, Sparky,</i>

04:52.326 --> 04:55.410
<i>taking his seventh inning</i>
<i>stroll around the infield</i>

04:55.412 --> 04:57.179
<i>with ballpark owner,</i>
<i>Lloyd Waterman.</i>

04:57.181 --> 04:58.647
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>Sparky on the mend,</i>

04:58.649 --> 05:00.883
<i>recently bitten by a raccoon.</i>

05:00.885 --> 05:03.018
ANNOUNCER 2:
Seems he's recovered just fine.

05:03.020 --> 05:04.420
<i>Welcome back, Sparky.</i>

05:04.422 --> 05:07.222
There he is.
Come here, Sparky.

05:07.224 --> 05:08.741
[GROWLING]

05:10.059 --> 05:11.526
[SCREAMING]

05:15.031 --> 05:16.064
[ALL GASPING]

05:16.066 --> 05:19.268
My star pitcher!
Somebody stop that dog!

05:19.270 --> 05:21.470
He's my dog.
I'll take care of it.

05:24.274 --> 05:25.740
I can't watch.

05:25.742 --> 05:28.410
Goodbye, Sparky.

05:28.412 --> 05:30.012
My patella.

05:30.014 --> 05:31.413
Oops.

05:33.249 --> 05:35.717
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>And down goes Sparky.</i>

05:35.719 --> 05:38.753
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>Third on-field execution</i>
<i>of an animal this season.</i>

05:38.755 --> 05:43.492
ANNOUNCER 1:
And who says baseball's boring?

05:43.494 --> 05:45.494
[♪]

05:48.931 --> 05:51.233
Cleveland, we're still going
to state, right?

05:51.235 --> 05:53.268
I got a lot
riding on this team.

05:53.270 --> 05:54.703
There's no way.

05:54.705 --> 05:57.839
Without Wilkerson, we're like
Kim Cattrall's bedroom.

05:57.841 --> 06:01.776
Eight scared teenage boys just
waiting for it all to be over.

06:01.778 --> 06:03.012
It's hopeless.

06:03.014 --> 06:04.779
HOLT:
Coach, you missed one.

06:04.781 --> 06:07.633
Heads up.

06:07.635 --> 06:09.284
Ow! Son of a bitch!

06:09.286 --> 06:11.419
Where'd you learn
to pitch like that?

06:11.421 --> 06:12.871
Play catch with my mom
every night.

06:12.873 --> 06:14.840
She says it tuckers me out.
It does.

06:14.842 --> 06:16.241
Move it, kid.

06:16.243 --> 06:18.527
Ha-ha! Holt looks like a kid.

06:18.529 --> 06:19.861
[THINKING]
<i>Wish he was a kid,</i>

06:19.863 --> 06:23.199
<i>so he could throw</i>
<i>that knuckleball for our team.</i>

06:23.201 --> 06:25.234
<i>Wait a minute.</i>

06:27.754 --> 06:30.556
<i>Hm. Hm?</i>

06:30.558 --> 06:32.792
ANNOUNCER 1:
And pitching for the Growlers,

06:32.794 --> 06:35.627
<i>rebel transfer student,</i>
<i>Colt Koufax.</i>

06:35.629 --> 06:38.196
Strike three.
<i>What a pitch from Koufax,</i>

06:38.198 --> 06:40.682
<i>which I believe</i>
<i>is a Jewish name.</i>

06:40.684 --> 06:42.701
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>Before you comment further,</i>
<i>Gordy,</i>

06:42.703 --> 06:45.037
<i>remember, everyone can hear</i>
<i>what you're saying.</i>

06:45.039 --> 06:48.607
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>Jews are fine by me.</i>
<i>Let's go, Growlers.</i>

06:50.776 --> 06:53.045
[♪]

06:53.047 --> 06:55.914
Wow, Colt, you're such
a good baseball player.

06:55.916 --> 06:59.567
And you're so mature
with your 5 o'clock shadow

06:59.569 --> 07:03.171
and your crow's feet
and your graying nose hair.

07:03.173 --> 07:05.507
Yeah, you look just like
the teenagers on TV.

07:05.509 --> 07:06.909
Yeah, I am pretty cool.

07:06.911 --> 07:09.744
But one time at my old school,
I took the whole day off.

07:09.746 --> 07:12.680
Me and my best friend, Cameron,
took his dad's Ferrari.

07:12.682 --> 07:13.815
Drove all around Chi-town,

07:13.817 --> 07:16.217
picked up my girlfriend,
Sloan Peterson,

07:16.219 --> 07:17.552
sang "Danke Schoen"
on a float.

07:17.554 --> 07:21.106
Meanwhile, Ben Stein's
going, "Bueller? Bueller?"

07:21.108 --> 07:23.241
Got home just in time.
Didn't even get caught.

07:23.243 --> 07:24.376
Chicka-ka!

07:24.378 --> 07:25.644
♪ Oh, oh

07:25.646 --> 07:27.112
Awesome!
Wow!

07:27.114 --> 07:29.748
Your sister
must hate you.

07:29.750 --> 07:31.267
[THINKING]
<i>Mmm.</i>

07:31.269 --> 07:33.335
<i>Donna, don't let yourself</i>
<i>fall in love</i>

07:33.337 --> 07:35.638
<i>with another</i>
<i>teenage bad boy.</i>

07:35.640 --> 07:38.039
<i>Especially one</i>
<i>who looks like...</i>

07:38.041 --> 07:39.508
Holt?

07:39.510 --> 07:41.560
Did she just
call you Holt?

07:41.562 --> 07:43.295
Uh, maybe. Don't care.

07:43.297 --> 07:45.997
Who cares what grown-ups say?
We're kids. Incorporated.

07:45.999 --> 07:49.000
Before your time. Our time.
Gotta go.

07:53.523 --> 07:55.524
Coach Brown, a word?

07:55.526 --> 07:56.792
Here we go.

07:56.794 --> 07:58.244
Hey, baby.

07:58.246 --> 08:00.312
Cleveland, tell me
you have nothing to do

08:00.314 --> 08:03.381
with your best friend pretending
to be a baseball player.

08:03.383 --> 08:05.450
You're my best friend,
Donna.

08:05.452 --> 08:08.320
Oh, really?

08:08.322 --> 08:10.355
No. What the hell
is going on?

08:10.357 --> 08:11.656
Cheating to get to state.

08:11.658 --> 08:12.758
I didn't hear that.

08:12.760 --> 08:14.559
I said,
cheating to get to s--

08:14.561 --> 08:16.461
Cleveland, I heard you.

08:16.463 --> 08:18.180
[♪]

08:23.519 --> 08:24.536
You're out!

08:24.538 --> 08:26.939
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

08:32.428 --> 08:33.528
You're out!

08:33.530 --> 08:35.480
[♪]

08:50.880 --> 08:53.682
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>And the Growlers</i>
<i>are one strike away.</i>

09:05.411 --> 09:06.712
You're out!

09:06.714 --> 09:08.731
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>Growlers go to state!</i>

09:08.733 --> 09:12.600
<i>My, oh, my. Championship game</i>
<i>tomorrow night.</i>

09:12.602 --> 09:15.220
A rematch of 1984,

09:15.222 --> 09:19.090
Stoolbend versus Mud Falls.

09:19.092 --> 09:21.360
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

09:22.595 --> 09:25.530
I think I'm getting
the hang of this.

09:25.532 --> 09:30.069
Hey, Junior, I just finished my
project. Wanna take a look see?

09:30.071 --> 09:31.770
Wow, it's great.

09:31.772 --> 09:33.305
And it gets even better.

09:33.307 --> 09:36.241
This sheet's just covering it
up, so it's a surprise.

09:36.243 --> 09:40.012
I'm gonna blow
Mr. Tanner's mind.

09:40.014 --> 09:42.147
Nuh-uh, nuh-uh.

09:42.149 --> 09:43.815
No, you did not.

09:43.817 --> 09:47.102
I'm blown away.
I'm blown away.

09:47.104 --> 09:48.670
No!

09:48.672 --> 09:50.238
[LAUGHS]

09:50.240 --> 09:54.109
Hey, thanks. So show me what
you've been working on all week.

09:54.111 --> 09:56.611
It's a wooden window holder
opener.

09:58.898 --> 10:00.599
I got it.

10:04.871 --> 10:07.940
Oh, man, what else
does that thing do?

10:07.942 --> 10:09.407
Well, there's this.

10:09.409 --> 10:11.610
[ANGELIC CHIMES PLAYING]

10:12.845 --> 10:16.215
Off to slay
the troll king.

10:16.217 --> 10:19.084
I think I misunderstood
the assignment.

10:19.086 --> 10:21.336
[♪]

10:21.338 --> 10:22.670
Drink up, little buddy.

10:22.672 --> 10:24.439
You've kept
my betting streak alive

10:24.441 --> 10:26.641
and got us
to the championships.

10:27.727 --> 10:29.828
Timmy, he don't know.

10:29.830 --> 10:33.432
Timmy, honest bear.

10:33.434 --> 10:35.550
Here's to Colt
and the Growlers.

10:35.552 --> 10:38.120
Tomorrow, we--
I mean, they win state.

10:38.122 --> 10:42.857
And I-- I mean, he gets laid for
the first time since 1997...

10:42.859 --> 10:44.359
when he was 4.

10:44.361 --> 10:45.994
I know
you're enjoying this,

10:45.996 --> 10:48.897
but you're supposed
to be keeping a low profile.

10:48.899 --> 10:50.232
Sorry, bro, no low pro.

10:50.234 --> 10:52.267
Please, at least wait
until tomorrow.

10:52.269 --> 10:56.671
After we beat Mud Falls
and I get that sweet state ring.

10:56.673 --> 10:57.890
Well, I gotta bizounce.

10:57.892 --> 10:59.892
A kid in my homeroom's parents
are out of town.

10:59.894 --> 11:02.961
Okay. But remember,
we got a big game tomorrow,

11:02.963 --> 11:05.931
so don't statutory
rape anybody.

11:05.933 --> 11:07.933
[BOTH LAUGH]

11:13.306 --> 11:15.123
[TIRES SQUEAL]
[ROCK MUSIC BLARING]

11:15.125 --> 11:16.908
Oh, Holt's home.

11:18.811 --> 11:21.230
Wait, what's Colt doing
driving Holt's car?

11:21.232 --> 11:22.897
He must have stolen it.

11:22.899 --> 11:24.699
And he drove right
to Holt's house.

11:24.701 --> 11:26.868
The balls on that kid.

11:26.870 --> 11:30.572
Yeah, Tim. I'll be sure to
reprimand him after the season.

11:30.574 --> 11:32.874
Now Colt is going
into Holt's house.

11:32.876 --> 11:34.843
We gotta stop him.

11:34.845 --> 11:36.161
[GROWLING]

11:36.163 --> 11:37.729
Stop it!
Stay away from Colt.

11:37.731 --> 11:39.597
Don't tase me, bro!
Stay away from Holt.

11:39.599 --> 11:42.067
Help! Beatles!
Your names are so similar,

11:42.069 --> 11:44.002
and you are of similar sizes.
I can't get up!

11:44.004 --> 11:46.104
Old people commercial!

11:46.106 --> 11:49.707
This just in.
Your star player wears a wig.

11:49.709 --> 11:52.110
Come on, Tim. I need that
for the game tomorrow.

11:54.063 --> 11:55.030
[GASPS]

11:55.032 --> 11:56.331
What in the wild,

11:56.333 --> 11:58.901
wild world of sports
is going on?

11:58.903 --> 12:01.236
Hey, Cleveland,
you're not gonna believe this,

12:01.238 --> 12:04.572
but, uh, Colt is, uh, is Holt.

12:04.574 --> 12:08.293
What? No. That--
That can't be true, he--

12:08.295 --> 12:11.446
Wait a minute, you knew.
You all knew.

12:11.448 --> 12:15.416
Look, I only need Holt to pitch
one more game tomorrow,

12:15.418 --> 12:18.286
and then Stoolbend
is state champs.

12:18.288 --> 12:19.787
Sure, it's cheating.

12:19.789 --> 12:21.857
But I'm doing it
for you, Tim.

12:21.859 --> 12:23.391
Can't you see that?

12:23.393 --> 12:26.761
All of this has been
for you and me.

12:26.763 --> 12:30.131
I'm sorry, Cleveland,
but cheating is morally wrong.

12:30.133 --> 12:31.833
Plus, Raymond
should be pitching.

12:31.835 --> 12:35.337
I'm sorry. I have no choice
but to report thi-- Ow!

12:35.339 --> 12:37.004
What the--?

12:37.006 --> 12:40.308
Hey, man, cut it out.
That's a shovel, you know?

12:40.310 --> 12:44.579
Why won't you go down?

12:44.581 --> 12:47.315
Okay, seriously, Lester,
it's getting really annoying.

12:47.317 --> 12:49.951
KENDRA:
For the championship!

12:49.953 --> 12:51.770
[HOWLING]

12:59.245 --> 13:02.047
Go Growlers.

13:05.084 --> 13:08.386
I'm freaking out.
I got blood on my hands, Lester.

13:08.388 --> 13:11.589
I gotta keep it together.
I gotta keep it togeth--

13:11.591 --> 13:12.841
Tim will be fine.

13:12.843 --> 13:15.594
I'll bring him back
right after the game tomorrow.

13:16.696 --> 13:17.896
[TIRES SCREECHING]

13:17.898 --> 13:19.548
This doesn't feel right.

13:19.550 --> 13:21.650
Like a vegan barbecue.

13:21.652 --> 13:25.570
All right. Not dogs
and shamburgers are ready.

13:26.972 --> 13:29.741
Hey, bro,
you want some fake-on on that?

13:29.743 --> 13:30.942
[SCREAMS]

13:30.944 --> 13:34.212
Smell that?
That's meat burning.

13:34.214 --> 13:38.783
Oh, God,
that smells so good.

13:41.120 --> 13:44.022
Okay, listen up.
It's almost game time.

13:44.024 --> 13:45.090
Where's Colt?

13:45.092 --> 13:46.174
Um...

13:46.176 --> 13:47.542
He quit.

13:47.544 --> 13:48.810
He's joining the musical.

13:48.812 --> 13:50.645
He said he had to be true
to who he is,

13:50.647 --> 13:52.614
not to who everyone
thought he was.

13:54.033 --> 13:56.384
Five, six, seven, eight.

13:56.386 --> 13:57.852
[DANCE MUSIC BLARING]

14:05.227 --> 14:07.562
What are you thinking?
This is the championship.

14:07.564 --> 14:10.232
Musical theater
is for the gays,

14:10.234 --> 14:13.168
the lucky, lucky gays.

14:14.903 --> 14:16.438
[SIGHS]

14:18.424 --> 14:21.559
Dad, why are you undressing
that little boy

14:21.561 --> 14:24.262
who has a chest tattoo
of Jeremy Piven

14:24.264 --> 14:26.364
just like Mr. Holt?

14:26.366 --> 14:28.733
Scram, Holt.
Get to the field.

14:28.735 --> 14:30.969
Wait, what's going on here?

14:30.971 --> 14:33.038
Why would you do this, Dad?

14:33.040 --> 14:34.839
Let me tell you
something, son.

14:34.841 --> 14:37.542
Sometimes the cards you're dealt
aren't good enough.

14:37.544 --> 14:39.644
You have to reach
for better cards.

14:39.646 --> 14:41.013
Cheating cards.

14:41.015 --> 14:42.680
But how can you live
with yourself

14:42.682 --> 14:44.649
when you're cheating to win?

14:44.651 --> 14:47.202
I'm just settling the score
with Coach Butler.

14:47.204 --> 14:49.937
Besides, it's tradition
to cheat in baseball.

14:49.939 --> 14:54.175
Look at Mark McGwire,
Roger Clemens, Alex Rodriguez,

14:54.177 --> 14:58.846
and the entire 2004 and 2007
Boston Red Sox.

14:58.848 --> 15:02.834
Sometimes you gotta do
whatever it takes to win.

15:02.836 --> 15:05.787
Now, come on,
we're gonna go win state.

15:05.789 --> 15:06.988
I'll be right there.

15:06.990 --> 15:09.725
I just remembered something
I need to do.

15:09.727 --> 15:12.460
[THINKING]
<i>I wonder what</i>
<i>he remembered to do.</i>

15:12.462 --> 15:15.129
<i>I wonder what Donna's</i>
<i>making for dinner.</i>

15:15.131 --> 15:18.032
<i>I wonder if she'll</i>
<i>even make dinner.</i>

15:18.034 --> 15:20.935
<i>I'll pick up some Pad Thai</i>
<i>and some scrambled eggs</i>

15:20.937 --> 15:23.104
<i>and a Clark bar</i>
<i>on the way home.</i>

15:23.106 --> 15:24.806
<i>If she's already made dinner,</i>

15:24.808 --> 15:27.108
<i>then I'll just eat that</i>
<i>for lunch tomorrow.</i>

15:27.110 --> 15:28.176
<i>[LAUGHING]</i>

15:28.178 --> 15:29.877
<i>Terry will be so jealous.</i>

15:29.879 --> 15:32.747
<i>He always has</i>
<i>crummy lunches.</i>

15:32.749 --> 15:35.917
<i>It's sad that Terry's alone.</i>

15:35.919 --> 15:37.652
[ORGAN PLAYING]

15:41.424 --> 15:43.541
Hey, old man.

15:43.543 --> 15:44.609
Get it?

15:44.611 --> 15:45.844
[BOTH LAUGH]

15:45.846 --> 15:47.679
Yes, I do get it.

15:47.681 --> 15:50.414
Oh, I'm happy
you're here, Rallo.

15:51.734 --> 15:52.700
You're out!

15:52.702 --> 15:54.636
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>Another strikeout.</i>

15:54.638 --> 15:56.787
<i>I haven't seen a pitching</i>
<i>performance rival this</i>

15:56.789 --> 15:59.991
<i>since Danny Almonte,</i>
<i>the kid who lied about his age</i>

15:59.993 --> 16:02.760
<i>to pitch in the Little League</i>
<i>World Series.</i>

16:02.762 --> 16:04.596
[OWLS HOOTING DISTANTLY]

16:06.632 --> 16:11.720
What the--? How did I get
in the woods?

16:11.722 --> 16:14.088
Oh, man,
stood up too fast.

16:14.090 --> 16:16.892
Oh, gross, sap.
I hate the woods.

16:16.894 --> 16:18.660
You gotta beam me out of here,
Jesus.

16:18.662 --> 16:20.662
I gotta haul bear ass
to that game

16:20.664 --> 16:22.597
and stop Cleveland
from cheating.

16:22.599 --> 16:25.801
If there was any way
to get to the field quick.

16:27.603 --> 16:31.223
Hm. That gives me an idea.

16:33.976 --> 16:35.760
Hey, thanks for the ride, Doug.

16:35.762 --> 16:38.029
Good luck with your wife's
operation.

16:38.031 --> 16:40.798
Oh, right. Don't worry,
honey, we're almost there.

16:40.800 --> 16:42.900
[WOMAN GROANING]

16:45.354 --> 16:48.423
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>Grab your gas can</i>
<i>and find a cop car,</i>

16:48.425 --> 16:51.893
<i>because two more outs</i>
<i>and Stoolbend is champs.</i>

16:51.895 --> 16:53.261
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>Hold everything.</i>

16:53.263 --> 16:56.847
<i>Here comes virgin</i>
<i>Principal Wally Farquhare.</i>

16:56.849 --> 16:58.883
Stop the game!
Stop the game!

16:58.885 --> 17:01.152
One of these students
is ineligible.

17:05.691 --> 17:08.593
Ernie Krinklesac
is the guilty Gus.

17:08.595 --> 17:11.329
He never turned in
his final wood shop project.

17:11.331 --> 17:13.364
What?
That gives him an F,

17:13.366 --> 17:15.399
which makes him
academically ineligible

17:15.401 --> 17:18.069
for extracurricular
activities.

17:18.071 --> 17:19.153
Whew!

17:19.155 --> 17:21.590
Hey, how did Ernie
fail shop?

17:21.592 --> 17:23.424
He built our carport.

17:23.426 --> 17:26.761
How? How indeed.

17:26.763 --> 17:29.180
I did what it took to win, Dad.

17:29.182 --> 17:31.616
<i>First, I created</i>
<i>a distraction.</i>

17:34.820 --> 17:37.388
<i>And then, for the final part</i>
<i>of my trick,</i>

17:37.390 --> 17:39.023
<i>known as the prestige,</i>

17:39.025 --> 17:42.460
<i>I took Ernie's project</i>
<i>and put my name on it.</i>

17:42.462 --> 17:44.729
How could you do that
to your friend?

17:44.731 --> 17:47.965
Like you said, winning is
the most important thing.

17:47.967 --> 17:50.935
Friend or no friend,
I gotta get mine.

17:50.937 --> 17:53.805
And if I failed shop,
I would disappoint you.

17:53.807 --> 17:56.408
And I've never ever
disappointed you, Daddy.

17:56.410 --> 17:59.911
Well, you did disappoint me
by cheating.

17:59.913 --> 18:02.647
What? Where do you think
I got the idea?

18:02.649 --> 18:05.049
You're cheating.
I learned it from you.

18:05.051 --> 18:07.084
You just found out
I was cheating.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.453
Ah, busted.

18:08.455 --> 18:11.222
Oh, Junior,
what have I taught you?

18:14.460 --> 18:17.545
You did good, Holt,
but the jig's up.

18:17.547 --> 18:19.230
Why are you taking me out, bro?

18:19.232 --> 18:20.999
This whole thing's wrong.

18:21.001 --> 18:24.436
Bad caramel.
Too much bad caramel.

18:24.438 --> 18:26.421
Give me the ball.

18:26.423 --> 18:29.257
Yeah, I get it.
It's probably for the best.

18:29.259 --> 18:32.560
All these 'roids
are doing a number on my junk.

18:36.248 --> 18:39.701
[ALL CHEERING]

18:39.703 --> 18:43.204
You're about to find out what
happens when animals attack.

18:43.206 --> 18:45.774
If you, uh, if you remember
those shows.

18:45.776 --> 18:49.510
Take it easy, Tim. I know you're
upset with me, but look.

18:49.512 --> 18:50.946
Um....

18:50.948 --> 18:53.114
Far away.

18:53.116 --> 18:55.049
Hello.

18:55.051 --> 18:56.651
Far away.

18:56.653 --> 18:59.553
That's my--
That's my Raymond.

18:59.555 --> 19:01.723
Yeah, Raymond. Go, buddy!

19:01.725 --> 19:04.726
I'm really sorry, Tim.
I know I messed up.

19:04.728 --> 19:06.260
Who cares, man?

19:06.262 --> 19:09.363
It's my son
in the championship game.

19:09.365 --> 19:11.416
ANNOUNCER 1:
Local burnout Raymond the bear,

19:11.418 --> 19:14.419
<i>not looking like he knows</i>
<i>where he is.</i>

19:15.721 --> 19:18.523
<i>Remember, that pitch</i>
<i>is not in slow motion</i>

19:18.525 --> 19:19.957
<i>to create dramatic effect.</i>

19:19.959 --> 19:21.959
<i>It's that slow.</i>

19:21.961 --> 19:25.146
ANNOUNCER 2:
<i>It's almost as if the ball</i>
<i>itself is stoned.</i>

19:27.415 --> 19:30.067
Bye-bye.

19:30.069 --> 19:31.469
ANNOUNCER 1:
<i>And there you have it.</i>

19:31.471 --> 19:33.271
<i>The Mud Falls Trotters</i>

19:33.273 --> 19:35.907
<i>are your state champions.</i>

19:35.909 --> 19:37.641
[ALL BOOING]

19:37.643 --> 19:40.996
You lose again,
Cold Brown.

19:40.998 --> 19:45.200
I guess my pitcher was just
a little bit better than yours.

19:48.820 --> 19:52.390
Well, Donna, he may have
the ring and the championship,

19:52.392 --> 19:55.192
but I have the comfort
of a clear conscience.

19:55.194 --> 19:57.662
I did a great thing
here today.

19:57.664 --> 20:00.732
Not really. You cheated
to get to the championship,

20:00.734 --> 20:03.668
and then wussed out and didn't
go through with it at the end.

20:03.670 --> 20:07.138
You realize you eliminated three
deserving teams from contention?

20:07.140 --> 20:08.906
So you really didn't
do anything great.

20:08.908 --> 20:10.074
No, I did.

20:10.076 --> 20:11.942
You don't get it.
It's guy stuff.

20:11.944 --> 20:14.579
Clear conscience, full hearts,
can't lose.

20:14.581 --> 20:18.483
Whatever. I'm just glad
I never knew anything about it.

20:19.501 --> 20:21.602
There's still time.

20:22.505 --> 20:27.842
♪ 525,600 minutes

20:27.844 --> 20:33.147
ALL:
♪ 525,000 journeys to plan

20:33.149 --> 20:38.252
♪ 525,600 minutes

20:38.254 --> 20:44.426
♪ How can you measure the life
Of a woman or a man? ♪

20:44.428 --> 20:47.562
No. No touch.

21:05.347 --> 21:07.848
[♪]

